        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-07-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-07-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="641" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d641">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">Marshall S. Carter</persName> to
                        General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-07-06">6 July
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93593. Following message transmitted to you at request of Acting Secretary of
                    State Dean Acheson:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Your 1053<note n="70" xml:id="d641fn70">July 5, <ref target="#pg_1297">p.
                                1297</ref>.</note> has my complete support. I understand that you
                        are in process of determining whether Doctor Stuart will be acceptable to
                        Chinese Government. I stand ready to take immediate action to <pb facs="1320" n="1308" xml:id="pg_1308"/> secure his appointment upon
                        receiving your final clearance. Signed Acheson Acting.”</p>
                </quote>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
